Description: Fragment of handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown.
Curator's comments: Name Aristogeitos. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 203, 2. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0071.41.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1003)
